/*!
@page geminidataanalytics-override-universe-domain How to Override the Default Universe Domain

In some cases, you may need to override the default universe domain used by the
client library. Use `AddUniverseDomainOption` when initializing the client
library to change this default.

<!-- inject-universe-domain-snippet-start -->
For example, this will override the default universe domain for `geminidataanalytics_v1::DataAgentServiceClient`:

@snippet data_agent_client_samples.cc set-client-universe-domain

Follow these links to find examples for other \c *Client classes:

- [\c geminidataanalytics_v1::DataAgentServiceClient](@ref geminidataanalytics_v1::DataAgentServiceClient-universe-domain-snippet)
- [\c geminidataanalytics_v1::DataChatServiceClient](@ref geminidataanalytics_v1::DataChatServiceClient-universe-domain-snippet)

<!-- inject-universe-domain-snippet-end -->

*/

// <!-- inject-universe-domain-pages-start -->

/*! @page geminidataanalytics_v1::DataAgentServiceClient-universe-domain-snippet Override geminidataanalytics_v1::DataAgentServiceClient Universe Domain

@snippet google/cloud/geminidataanalytics/v1/samples/data_agent_client_samples.cc set-client-universe-domain

*/

